<TITLE> Govt declares junior secondary syllabus </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 06 (bdnews24.com)  The government on Tuesday declared the syllabus for Junior School Certificate Examinations. The junior secondary finals for students finishing eighth grade, are going to be held for the first time in November this year. The examinations will be held out of 900 marks and results will be published in a GPA (grade point average) system, said an official on Tuesday. The JSC syllabus will be available on websites of the education ministry, Dhaka Education Board and Inter-Education Board. The web addresses are respectively www.moedu.gov.bd, www.dhakaeducationboard.gov.bd and www.educationboard.gov.bd. The circular also said that academic transcripts will be issued instead of mark sheets. The students will need to submit these transcripts for admission in ninth grade. Students must be at least 11 years old to be admitted to grade 8 but must not be over 17 years of age. bd
